<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-19-0939 </DOCNO><TEXT>Within the scope of the reorganization of the energy distribution a newenergy company has been set up in the horticultural region Westland.This company sells annually about 1.1 billion m/sup 3/ of natural gasto 36.000 clients. For greenhouse market gardeners combined heat andpower generation is an attractive option. In order to make large-scaleapplication possible the energy company itself has undertaken the operationof CHP installations since this enables the capacity of the installationsto be adapted to the higher heat demand of the greenhouse market gardeners,while the surplus electricity generated is feeded to the public network.The experiences with these installations are discussed. 8 figs., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>